#     - toolkit/components/content-classifier/content_classifier_engine/src/lib.rs
#     - toolkit/components/content-classifier/content_classifier_engine/Cargo.toml
#
Extend the upstream FF152 content-classifier component with native COSMETIC
element-hiding (the gjoa adblock M2 feature).

- Rust FFI: url_cosmetic_resources + hidden_class_id_selectors (+ fill_cstr_thinvec)
- IDL: getUrlCosmeticResources + getHiddenClassIdSelectors (new uuid)
- C++ engine wrappers + cross-engine union in the service
- @mozilla.org/content-classifier-service;1 contract (GetSingleton) so JS can
  reach the MAIN_PROCESS_ONLY service
- moz.build: register GjoaCosmetic{Parent,Child}.sys.mjs as EXTRA_JS_MODULES
  (those NEW actor files ship as src/gjoa overlays, not in this patch)

